<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="1663" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1663">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.00/2364.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Jefferson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-10">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 10, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>American Consul at Bluefields telegraphs that he is informed that
                            insurrection of Creoles in Mosquito Territory is imminent. I should
                            consider it advisable for moral effect that the Department suggest to
                            the Secretary of the Navy the sending of a cruiser to Bluefields, and
                            that. Americans there should again be reminded through the Consul that
                            protection can not be extended to those implicated in any uprising
                            against the Nicaraguan Government.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Jefferson</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>